# Standard App Header Style

This rule defines the standard appearance for headers on navigable sub-screens (screens with a back button).

## Implementation

Use `useEffect` and `navigation.setOptions` within the screen component.

```javascript
import React, { useEffect } from 'react';
import { TouchableOpacity, Text } from 'react-native';
import { useNavigation } from 'expo-router';

const MyScreen = () => {
  const navigation = useNavigation();

  useEffect(() => {
    navigation.setOptions({
      title: 'Screen Title', // Set dynamically if needed
      headerStyle: {
        backgroundColor: '#F8F8F8', // Light gray background
      },
      headerTintColor: '#333333', // Dark text/icon color
      headerTitleStyle: {
        fontWeight: '600',
        fontSize: 17, // Standard title size
      },
      headerBackTitleVisible: false, // Hide back button text on iOS
      // Optional: Add a right button like in CreateEvent
      // headerRight: () => (
      //   <TouchableOpacity onPress={handleAction} style={{ marginRight: 15 }}>
      //     <Text style={{ color: '#007AFF', fontSize: 17, fontWeight: '600' }}>Action</Text>
      //   </TouchableOpacity>
      // ),
    });
  }, [navigation]); // Add relevant dependencies if title/actions change

  // ... rest of component
};
```

## Key Style Properties

- **Background Color:** `#F8F8F8` (Light Gray)
- **Tint Color (Text/Icons):** `#333333` (Dark Gray)
- **Title Font Weight:** `600`
- **Back Button:** Default arrow, no text label.

